A simple module that adds the switch case functionality to Python.  

To use:
1) Place PySwitch somewhere in your PYTHONPATH

2) Import switch from PySwitch.py   
from PySwitch import switch

3) Create a while loop calling the switch function with the value you want to check for.
while switch(birthyear):

3) Write if case(value) for each case you want to check.
if case(1996):
  print ("You must be at least 18 years old to view this website.")
  break #Note you can use break statements like the C switchcases.

4) Call the default function for a default case.
if default:
  print ("This is the default case")
  break

Note that by calling the switch function, the case and default functions are 
automatically added to builtins.
An example of usage can be seen in the switchtest.py file. 
